{
  "stem": "21626.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 78,
      "text": "But as she sat between my sister and me in the back as the car sped to the station, I looked at her face, and I could see tears in her eyes.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 79,
      "text": "And I could see how pale she was.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 80,
      "text": "And I suddenly realized how much she loved us both.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 81,
      "text": "And, and I was glad that Mother had such a nice sister.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 82,
      "text": "And I was to be gladder still in latter years.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 83,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Saying goodbye at the Wilson Station in Prague in the middle of the night was very hard.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 84,
      "text": "The platform was filled with anxious parents and German soldiers.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 85,
      "text": "And Mother and Father bravely smiled at us until the time came for the train to leave.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 86,
      "text": "And I cried impulsively, see you again in a free Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 87,
      "text": "And suddenly everybody looked horrified and frightened.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 88,
      "text": "Luckily, the German soldiers didn't understand because they had instructions to, for any reasons, whatever to, to snatch a child and, you know, keep them there if anybody give any reasons.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 89,
      "text": "And as the train [INAUDIBLE] from the station, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] my parents were crying, though they still tried to smile, you know, as they waved us goodbye.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 90,
      "text": "And suddenly I was so glad when my sister's hand reached for mine, and I realized I still had her.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 91,
      "text": "And she confirmed this in the same very words.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 92,
      "text": "She said, you'll always have me, come what may.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 93,
      "text": "You can always turn to me.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 94,
      "text": "I'll be there for you.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 95,
      "text": "And this sister whom I didn't particularly like, you know, being the elder bossy sister, suddenly changed into a guardian angel.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 96,
      "text": "And she remained so all through the years of the war.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
